<para id="RM000000PNJ00IX" category="J" type-id="303UF" name-id="NS0W1-01" from="200601">
<dtccode/>
<dtcname>Illumination for Panel Switch does not Come on with Tail Switch ON</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000PNJ00IX_01" type-id="51" category="05">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000PNJ00IX_02" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM000000PNJ00IX_02_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___00004XI00000">
<testtitle>CHECK VEHICLE SIGNAL (DISPLAY CHECK MODE)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the "Display Check" mode (Vehicle Signal Check Mode) (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM0000011BV00GX"/>).</ptxt>
</test1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="I038223E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check that the display changes between ON and OFF according to the light control switch operation.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Light Control Switch</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Display</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>TAIL or ON</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>ON</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>OFF</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>OFF</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<atten4>
<ptxt>This display is updated once per second. As a result, it is normal for the display to lag behind the actual change in the switch.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test1>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM000000PNJ00IX_02_0002" fin="true">OK</down>
<right ref="RM000000PNJ00IX_02_0003" fin="true">NG</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM000000PNJ00IX_02_0002">
<testtitle>REPLACE RADIO AND NAVIGATION ASSEMBLY</testtitle>
</testgrp>
